projectsArray.Title: Reaction Timer
projectsArray.About: This is a project used to practice using Vue.js directives, specifically, the '@click' directive. The 'play' button is clicked, and then the user tests their reaction speed and waits somewhere between 1-5 seconds and immediately clicks the pop up div

projectsArray.Title: Vue Framework Form
projectsArray.About: This is a project that shows I understand how to use the Vue.js' v-model and value-binding in a form. The user enters information into the form, and the form updates the information at the bottom of the page.

projectsArray.Title: Tailwind Landing Page
projectsArray.About: This is a project that shows the usage of the low-level tailwind css framework to create a landing page for the 'manage' company.

projectsArray.Title: Vue Covid Tracker
projectsArray.About: This project shows the usage of both the Vue.js and Tailwind css frameworks. This project also shows the usage of an api endpoint from covid19api.com. The application keeps track of all the covid cases both globally and by country.
